text: Iskra () is a rural locality (a village) in Austrumsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 124 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 24 km from Iglino, 4 km from Austrum. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Iskra, Republic of Bashkortostan
